parameters: \pop[2]Everything is happening a mile a minute.

\pop[2]Messing with their security and opening doors we didn't have access to?

\pop[2]But it basically breaks the number one rule in our entire society.

\pop[2]Tools like these, placed in the wrong hands, could cause irreparable damage.
\pop[2]I can only hope that Isaac never lets them see the light of day.
\pop[2]Stuff that can endanger us, and others, should be destroyed after today...

\pop[3]You know, after all of this is over?
\pop[3]I've never really been to one before.
\c[14]Or\c[0] learned how to swim, for that matter.
There's a pool in the rec center near my library.

\pop[3]They basically made you who you are.

It's looking pretty run down lately. Could definitely use some aid.

I wanna go on tour, too.

\pop[2]If we wanted to make them a reality, we'd have no choice but to succeed.
\pop[2]Even if they seem a little uncharacteristic of them, it was still something to hold onto.
\pop[2]When this blows over, I doubt he'd be going on tour with Klace.
\pop[2]He'd likely unite with his colony friends, and show them the city.
\pop[2]I start to think about what I'd like to do, but then the car comes to a stop.
\pop[2]It was a bit sudden, and I'm jerked forward, ending my daydreams.
\pop[2]I look out the window, and see a massive, majestic building.

\pop[2]It seems completely dead, and silent. Almost nobody is around.

\pop[2]When we enter the building, I'm immediately taken aback...
